---
/**
 * LandingIntroPanel — the framed serif paragraph that opens every
 * category landing page.
 *
 * Extracted from per-category `.xx-landing__intro-text` rules that
 * were pixel-identical across FM, TD, RF, and EP. All four read:
 *
 *   · serif face at clamp(md, 1.4vw, lg)
 *   · snug line-height
 *   · text-wrap: pretty (no global reading-max; the panel owns its
 *     own reading width — see docs/design-direction.md §Reading width)
 *   · 3px black frame on white surface
 *   · padding: --space-5
 *
 * Takes a default slot so callers can use inline <strong>, <em>, etc.
 * without having to pass HTML through props. Intentionally has no
 * props — the visual contract is fixed so the four categories stay
 * in lockstep.
 */
---
<p class="nsb-landing-intro">
  <slot />
</p>

<style>
  .nsb-landing-intro {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(var(--text-md), 1.4vw, var(--text-lg));
    line-height: var(--leading-snug);
    text-wrap: pretty;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin: 0;
    padding: var(--space-5);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 3px solid var(--color-frame);
    /* No reading-max cap — the panel itself owns its own reading
       width. See docs/design-direction.md §Reading width. */
    max-width: none;
  }
</style>
